Abstract: We give a lower bound of (f bd=2c ) for the number of vertices of a d-dimensional polytope with f facets which can appear on the outer boundary of a projection to any dimension 2 k &lt; d. By duality, this implies a lower bound of (n bd=2c ) for the number of facets in a k-dimensional slice of a d-dimensional polytope with n vertices. At the same time, the Upper Bound Theorem provides an O(n bd=2c ) upper bound for this quantity. For cyclic polytopes, however, we show an upper bound of O(n) on this quantity in dimension four. We give a new algorithm for the construction of the boundary of the projection. 
