Reference-contexts: One optimization problem is the maximization of a convex function in k variables x 1 ; : : : ; x k over a polytope P . The maximum is achieved at some vertex of the k-shadow. In <ref> [AAAS] </ref> this maximization is applied to finding the largest similar copy of one convex polygon contained in another, a problem with applications in vision and robotics. The computation of shadows was studied in [PoFa] and [PSSBM].
